    #games
      h1 games
      p Games are my passion, and I've designed them during and since my college days (ca. 2013).  I've run the design gamut, from level progression and layout, to asset creation, to music, to 3D modeling, to writing, the list goes on.  Programming, however...let's just say that most projects involve countless conditionals and a mess of spaghetti code.
      p That said, more information below:
      .container
        #neci.box
        #hawk.box
        #mem.box
        #soon.box
      
      #necisnightmare.page
        img(src='https://placehold.it/300x300')
        h3 GBJam 2016 Entry: Neci's Nightmare
        p(md) In a blaze of inspiration I was compelled to create something for 2016's GBJam, and I felt it had to be related to an upcoming project. Thus, *Neci's Nightmare* was born!  It's a short "How long can you last?" type of game featuring the protagonist from that project, in which she runs from beasts in her nightmares.  Give it a shot on Windows via its [itch.io page](https://enmod.itch.io/necis-nightmare)!
        
      #hawkz.page
        img(src='https://placehold.it/300x300')
        h3 Hawk-Z
        p(md) You can find my senior games course project [on GitHub](https://github.com/EnMod/Hawk-Z), where you can download the master and try it out on Windows.  It's more or less a Starfox clone with a little narrative thrown in, and lasts until the boss is met (not fought).  I wore so many hats on this one, but that's par for the course with a small team as we all wore about as many.
      
      #memorylane.page
        img(src='https://placehold.it/300x300')
        h3 Memory Lane
        p(md) I also did a case study of sorts for my TCNJ capstone project, [also on Github](https://github.com/EnMod/Memory-Lane'), regarding the effects of advanced human-computer interaction on an otherwise passive video game experience. Mind, this project uses motion tracking tech that has since become vaporware, more details in the readme. Once I get my hands on an HTC Vive I'll be bringing the idea up to speed!
      
      #upcomingprojects.page
        img(src='https://placehold.it/300x300')
        h3 Upcoming Projects
        p(md) Currently I'm working on an ARPG in the style of Diablo and Torchlight, which is in the last stages of pre-production planning. Also in the works is an autobiographical adventure heavily inspired by elements of Makai Toushi SaGa and the Star Ocean series. More on those further in 2017!
      
    #stories
      h1 stories
      p If there's one thing I'd say I'm decent at, it's storytelling. I always enjoy giving life to a world through visual design, characters, plot, insane thematic elements, anything I can illustrate through whatever becomes my medium.
      p(md) For all of my written word including prose, poetry, musings, and reviews, you can peruse [my blog](https://blog.noelquiles.com)! Check out these categories:
